---
description: Database conventions for Adonis.
globs: apps/api/database/migrations/**
---

### Things to know

- I never add the `down` function in my migration files because I never use it.

### Column ordering in new tables

- When creating a new table via migration, always order columns with the primary key (`id`) first, then all other columns in alphabetical order.

### Adding new columns to existing tables

- When adding a new column to an existing table via migration, use `.after('column_name')` to place it in alphabetical order relative to the existing columns.
- Always check the existing Adonis model to determine the correct alphabetical position.
